/*Problem Description:

You are a Data Analyst at an online store. The finance team wants to identify all orders where the order value is above the overall average order value - these are high-value orders worth tracking for customer relationship management.

The result must contain the following columns:

order_id
customer_name
product_name
order_value*/


select order_id,
customer_name,
product_name,
order_value 
from shop_orders
where order_value >
(select avg(order_value) from shop_orders)
order by order_value desc
